casebody.data:
Argued April 23, STATE OF OREGON, Respondent, v. MICHAEL CAVANAUGH, Appellant. (No. C 72-08-2511 Cr) 508 P2d 817 Gary D. Babcock, Public Defender, Salem, argued the cause and filed the brief for appellant. John H. Clough, Assistant Attorney General, Salem, argued the cause for respondent. With him on the brief were Lee Johnson, Attorney General, and John W. Osburn, Solicitor General, Salem.

affirmed April 23, 1973

Before Schwab, Chief Judge, and Foley and Fort, Judges.
